# Rule Index

This file is intentionally small. Detailed rules are split by responsibility so the rule set can grow without becoming hard to maintain.

Read these rules as needed:

- `00-project.mdc`: Project identity, operating model, and shared priorities.
- `01-obsidian.mdc`: Vault structure, Markdown conventions, and durable memory rules.
- `02-typescript.mdc`: TypeScript and data modeling rules.
- `03-react.mdc`: React and Next.js component rules.
- `04-ui.mdc`: Dark glassmorphism, drag and drop, node-based UI direction.
- `05-task-system.mdc`: Task, project, decision, and preference system behavior.
- `06-documentation.mdc`: README, specs, decisions, and note maintenance.
- `07-git.mdc`: Git hygiene and repository safety rules.
- `08-quality.mdc`: Verification, testing, accessibility, and review expectations.

Start with `00-project.mdc`, then apply the specialized rule that matches the work.
